<article>
    <h1>DRIVE CARE&#xAD;FULLY NEAR ROADS USED BY WILDLIFE</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201106/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-06"><time>2020-11-06</time></a>
        - <span>FORUM</span>
        - <span role="byline">Sabrina Ab&#xAD;dul Jab&#xAD;bar</span>
    </section>

    <p>The 200km drive around Sin­ga­pore fea­tured in The Straits Times (The 200km S’pore road trip, Oct 31) in­cluded Ri­fle Range Road and Old Up­per Thom­son Road. Those two roads are very nar­row and cut through for­est frag­ments, act­ing as ur­ban cor­ri­dors used fre­quently by wildlife such as macaques (left) and wild boars.</p>
    <p>I am part of a group that is work­ing to­gether with the Land Trans­port Au­thor­ity to work on mea­sures to re­duce the num­ber of an­i­mals killed on the road.</p>
    <p>These in­clude ed­u­cat­ing mo­torists to drive mind­fully and cau­tiously near these roads.</p>

